
<h1>Search it, Buy it!</h1>
<div class="forms">
    <form action="/register" method="POST">
        {{!-- 
            1)A label and an input are connected by an id(input) and a for(label)
            2)The input [type] determines its functionality: text, password, email
            3)[name] is for the naming the form <node /> for the backend API (also the widget (or "column names" in your db))
            4)[value] is the actual string text
            5)[placeholder] placeholder text
            x)An input with a [type=submit] will submit the whole form
              We can specify the type of request or [method] we want GET, POST, DELETE, PUT
              and which route we want to go with [action]
            
            y)[name] attributes should have camelCase for consistency in js
            z)bem methodology ./#blockName-elemName_modName_modVal
            --}}

        <div class="errors">
            {{#each messages}}
            <p>{{this}}</p>
            {{/each}}
        </div>


        <label for="form-username">
            Username
        </label>
        <input class="form-input" type="text" id="form-username-register" name="username" placeholder="Username" autocomplete="off"
            value="{{ uName }}" />

        <label for="form-email">
            Email
        </label>
        <input {{!-- type="email"  // Commented for assignment purposes --}} type="text" id="form-email" name="emailRegister"
            class="form-input" placeholder="Email" autocomplete="off" value="{{ email }}" />
        <label for="form-password">
            Password
        </label>
        <input class="form-input" id="form-password-register" type="password" name="passwordRegister" placeholder="Password"
            {{!-- autocomplete="off" --}} />


        <input class="form-button" id="form-submit" type="submit" value="SIGN UP" />
    </form>
    
    <form action="/login" method="POST">

        <div class="errors">
            {{#each messages}}
            <p>{{this}}</p>
            {{/each}}
        </div>

        <label for="form-email">
            Email
        </label>
        <input class="form-input" type="text" id="form-email-login" name="emailLogin" placeholder="Email" autocomplete="off" value="{{ email }}" />
        <label for="form-password">
            Password
        </label>
        <input class="form-input" id="form-password-login" type="password" name="passwordLogin" placeholder="Password" />

        <input class="form-button" id="login-button" type="submit" value="LOGIN" />
    </form>

</div>

<script src="js/cookie.js" type="text/javascript"></script>